content.text: table is designed to store historical data about custom report aliases. This table serves as an audit or versioning mechanism, capturing changes over time to the aliases used in custom reports. Each record in the table represents a specific version of a custom report alias, detailing its attributes and the time period during which it was valid.

The complexity level of this table is considered medium. While the table structure itself is straightforward, the historical nature of the data and the potential relationships with other tables (e.g., those storing current alias configurations or report definitions) add complexity. The presence of datetime fields for versioning and potential foreign key relationships also contribute to this assessment.
